      • flush

        public void flush(GatheringByteChannel file,
         boolean clear)
           throws UnsupportedOperationException
        Not supported because we want to guarantee you only ever clear an instance after it has been closed.
        Overrides:
        flush in class SortedTableBuilder
        Parameters:
        file - typically a FileChannel
        clear - if true, then the SortedTableBuilder.clear() is called on return. The reason why the parameter is offered is it's marginally more efficient to pass true than to pass false and followed by clear().
